snippet.textDisplay: “To become successful, inequality is not a problem. Anyone can make it.” Anyone else get so angry at that. If everyone went out to try and start their own business and become a millionaire we’d A) have a lot of broke people and B) these millionaires wouldn’t have anyone to do their nails, cook their food, do their plastic surgery. If you’re working hard it doesn’t make any sense to me why one occupation should make more than another unless it’s way more work, more risk etc. Veterinary technicians work long hours, are basically nurses but for animals, have to deal with a lot of emotional stress, but where I live (Canada) they barely make over minimum wage. This is just one example of a difficult job where people don’t get paid nearly enough. No one should sit on their ass all day doing fuck all and get paid, but these self made millionaires aren’t the only ones who work hard. Many people work their asses off and don’t become wealthy. No one should be a millionaire, no one needs that much money. Why does your hard work deserve more money than someone else’s? I think these millionaires forget that the only reason they’re millionaires in the first place is because other people are barely getting by, if they’re getting by at all. The only reason millionaires, billionaires exist is entirely because of inequality.
